14/01/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- EU security chief Javier Solana will visit Belgrade next week in an effort to spur Serbia to step up war crimes co-operation. Solana will also discuss Serbia-Montenegro's EU integration prospects. 
In other news, ethnic Albanian political leaders in southern Serbia decided to put off until the weekend a decision on sending representatives to a new co-ordination centre. The leaders say they must become more familiar with plans for the new structure, formed after the fatal weekend shooting of a teenager by Serbian border guards. (Beta, B92 - 13/01/05)
